            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Note that \"regular\" C extension classes do not exhibit this problem as their method implementations are automatically guarded by a type check:\r\n```python\r\n>>> import numpy as np\r\n>>> np.ndarray.byteswap(0)\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  Cell In[5], line 1\r\n    np.ndarray.byteswap(0)\r\nTypeError: descriptor 'byteswap' for 'numpy.ndarray' objects doesn't apply to a 'int' object\r\n```\r\n",
